{62552=AUBURN, Alabama (Ticker) -- Carnell Williams rushed for 204 
yards and two touchdowns on 26 carries as Auburn defeated
Alabama, 28-23, in the 68th Iron Bowl.

Williams wasted no time, ripping off an 80-yard TD run on the
first play from scrimmage, and the Tigers held off a
second-half Alabama charge to win consecutive games against the
Crimson Tide for the first time since 1988-89.

Auburn snapped a two-game losing streak, closing an up-and-down
regular season at 7-5, including 5-3 in the Southeastern
Conference West Division.

Alabama (4-8, 2-6) completes Mike Shula's first season as coach
next week at Hawaii.

John Vaughn kicked a 22-yard field goal with 4:07 left in the
second quarter to give Auburn an 18-2 halftime lead, but Brandon
Brooks sparked the Alabama comeback by returning the second
half kickoff 96 yards for a score.

The Crimson Tide closed to 18-16 on Shaud Williams' six-yard TD
run with 9:06 to go in the third, but Auburn increased its
advantage to 28-16 on Vaughn's 32-yard field goal and Carnell
Williams' one-yard TD run with seven minutes left.

With just over a minute left, Alabama's Brodie Croyle threw a
14-yard TD pass to Lance Taylor, who made the grab in the back
of the end zone after the ball was batted in the air by Triandos
Luke.

Croyle completed 13-of-29 passes for 180 yards with two
interceptions for the Crimson Tide. Shaud Williams chipped in
with 93 yards on 18 carries.

Auburn's Jason Campbell overcame two interceptions to complete
18-of-27 passes for 270 yards.}
